# Cursor AI Rules for Hy-lee Shopify Theme

## Project Type
This is a Shopify theme project using Liquid templating. NOT React/TypeScript.

## Context Files
Before making changes, read:
- docs/DEVELOPMENT_GUIDELINES.md
- docs/COMPONENT_INVENTORY.md
- docs/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md

## Component-First Development

### Rule: Check Before Create
ALWAYS check `theme/snippets/` before creating any UI element.
If a component exists, USE IT. If not, CREATE IT FIRST as a reusable snippet.

### Rule: Component Location
All UI components MUST be in `theme/snippets/` as `.liquid` files.

### Rule: Styling Location
Component styles MUST be in `theme/assets/component-{name}.css`.
NEVER use inline styles. NEVER hardcode colors or spacing.

## Design Tokens
ALWAYS use CSS custom properties from `theme-variables.css`:
```css
/* ✅ Correct */
color: var(--color-primary);
padding: var(--spacing-md);
font-size: var(--font-size-base);

/* ❌ Wrong */
color: #4A90A4;
padding: 16px;
```

## File Naming Conventions
- Components: `{name}.liquid`
- Component CSS: `component-{name}.css`
- Section CSS: `section-{name}.css`
- Template CSS: `template-{name}.css`

## CSS Naming (BEM)
```css
.component-name { }
.component-name__element { }
.component-name--modifier { }
```

## Documentation Updates
When completing work:
- New component → Update `docs/COMPONENT_INVENTORY.md`
- Completed task → Update `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md`
- Architecture decision → Update `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`

## Branching
Format: `{type}({scope}): {description}`
Types: feat, fix, chore, docs, style, test, refactor

## Commands
```bash
pnpm theme:dev          # Start dev server
pnpm theme-check        # Run Shopify linter
pnpm format             # Format code
pnpm theme:push         # Deploy to Shopify
pnpm test               # Run unit tests
pnpm test:e2e           # Run E2E tests
pnpm validate:structure # Check directory structure
```

## DO NOT
- Create React/TypeScript components
- Hardcode colors, spacing, or design values
- Create inline styles
- Duplicate components from `theme/snippets/`
- Skip documentation updates
